01:18.200 --> 01:21.431
I was Flint's first mate
that voyage...

01:21.520 --> 01:24.592
three days east of Tortola
in the Caribie.

01:24.680 --> 01:27.035
Flint knew an island.

01:27.120 --> 01:29.111
That's where we buried
the treasure.

01:29.200 --> 01:33.273
Gold and blood,
they were Flint's trademarks.

01:33.360 --> 01:36.238
He'd leave both
behind him that day.

01:40.400 --> 01:43.995
<i>Shiver my timbers</i>
<i>Shiver my soul</i>

01:44.080 --> 01:47.117
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

01:47.200 --> 01:51.352
<i>There are men whose hearts</i>
<i>are as black as coal</i>

01:51.440 --> 01:53.908
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

01:54.000 --> 01:57.549
<i>And they sailed their ship</i>
<i>'cross the ocean blue</i>

01:57.640 --> 02:00.632
<i>A bloodthirsty captain</i>
<i>and a cutthroat crew</i>

02:00.720 --> 02:04.315
<i>It's as dark a tale</i>
<i>as was ever told</i>

02:04.400 --> 02:09.520
<i>Of the lust for treasure</i>
<i>and the love of gold</i>

02:09.600 --> 02:13.832
<i>Shiver my timbers</i>
<i>Shiver my sides</i>

02:13.920 --> 02:16.275
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

02:16.360 --> 02:19.989
<i>There are hungers as strong</i>
<i>as the winds and tides</i>

02:20.080 --> 02:22.878
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

02:22.960 --> 02:26.714
<i>And those buccaneers</i>
<i>drown their sins in rum</i>

02:26.800 --> 02:30.076
<i>The devil himself would</i>
<i>have to call them scum</i>

02:30.160 --> 02:33.596
<i>Every man aboard would have</i>
<i>killed his mate</i>

02:33.680 --> 02:37.229
<i>For a bag of guineas</i>
<i>or a piece of eight</i>

02:37.320 --> 02:39.151
<i>A piece of eight</i>

02:39.240 --> 02:42.710
<i>-A piece of eight</i>
<i>-A five, six, seven, eight</i>

02:42.800 --> 02:45.598
<i>Hulla wacka, ulla wacka</i>
<i>Something not right</i>

02:45.680 --> 02:49.434
<i>Many wicked icky things</i>
<i>gonna happen tonight</i>

02:49.520 --> 02:51.988
<i>Hulla wacka, moolah wacka</i>
<i>Sailor man beware</i>

02:52.080 --> 02:56.073
<i>When de money in de ground</i>
<i>Dere's murder in de air</i>

02:56.160 --> 02:57.991
<i>Murder in the air</i>

02:58.080 --> 02:59.832
One more time now.

02:59.920 --> 03:02.878
<i>Shiver my timbers</i>
<i>Shiver my bones</i>

03:02.960 --> 03:06.236
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

03:06.320 --> 03:10.632
<i>There are secrets that sleep</i>
<i>with old Davy Jones</i>

03:10.720 --> 03:12.950
<i>Yo ho, heave ho</i>

03:13.040 --> 03:16.316
<i>When the mainsail's set</i>
<i>and the anchor's weighed</i>

03:16.400 --> 03:19.995
<i>There's no turning back</i>
<i>from any course that's laid</i>

03:20.080 --> 03:23.675
<i>And when greed and villainy</i>
<i>sail the sea</i>

03:23.760 --> 03:28.959
<i>You can bet your boots</i>
<i>there'll be treachery</i>

03:37.640 --> 03:40.950
<i>Shiver my timbers</i>
<i>Shiver my sails</i>

03:41.040 --> 03:43.429
<i>Dead men tell no tales</i>

03:45.680 --> 03:49.434
Oh, aye. Fifteen men
went ashore that day...

03:49.520 --> 03:53.308
and only Flint, his own self,
returned.

03:53.800 --> 03:56.155
Oh, aye, and then old Flinty...

03:56.240 --> 04:00.313
up and died afore they could get
back to that cursed island...

04:00.400 --> 04:02.630
and dig up the treasure.

04:02.720 --> 04:07.191
No one knows to this day
who has old Flint's map.

04:07.280 --> 04:10.556
Now, isn't that a story
worth the hearing?

04:10.640 --> 04:13.279
It was the first dozen
times we heard it.

04:13.360 --> 04:15.999
I'll drink to that.

04:16.079 --> 04:19.038
But who has
the map now, huh?

04:19.120 --> 04:22.829
Some black-hearted,
squid-suckin' buccaneer?

04:22.920 --> 04:26.549
Or maybe it's
our very own Jim Hawkins.

04:26.640 --> 04:28.471
Eh,Jimmy?

04:28.560 --> 04:31.518
If I had it, my friends and I wouldn't
be here serving you rum, Mr Bones.

04:31.600 --> 04:33.989
That's right. We'd be out
searching for that treasure...

04:34.080 --> 04:36.913
sailing the seven seas
on a five-year mission...

04:37.000 --> 04:40.072
boldly going where no man
has gone before.

04:40.160 --> 04:42.390
- Say, that's catchy.
- Huh. Not me.

04:42.480 --> 04:46.473
If I had that treasure map,
I'd be tradin' it for a decent meal.

04:46.560 --> 04:48.790
Hey, Gonzo, you think
he's gonna eat this?

04:48.880 --> 04:52.953
Aye! Beware the one-legged man!
He's the one to fear!

04:53.040 --> 04:54.712
Don't worry, Captain.
We'll watch for him.

04:54.800 --> 04:57.519
Yeah, I'll watch for him,
if he's deliverin' a pizza.

04:59.360 --> 05:01.271
Even old Flinty
feared him.

05:01.360 --> 05:05.114
If he comes pokin' 'round here,
you run for me whippety-quick!

05:05.200 --> 05:07.760
- If we see him, we'll tell you.
- Yeah. One leg, three heads...

05:07.840 --> 05:09.671
couple of dozen noses--
if anything weird happens--

05:09.760 --> 05:12.797
And it'll be nay
jokin' matter, hose nose.

05:12.880 --> 05:15.838
The one-legged man
brings death.

05:15.920 --> 05:18.229
Time, gentlemen!

05:18.320 --> 05:20.151
It's closing time!

05:20.240 --> 05:22.390
Ya pays your bills,
and then ya shove off.

05:22.480 --> 05:24.436
Go on. Out ya go!

05:26.880 --> 05:29.189
Oh, you're drunk again,
are ya?

05:29.280 --> 05:32.158
Boys, look at the state
of this place!

05:32.240 --> 05:34.549
How comes it gets to be
such a pigsty, huh?

05:34.640 --> 05:36.471
Pigsty? Hey!

05:36.560 --> 05:38.710
No offence meant, gentlemen, sirs.
No offence meant.

05:38.800 --> 05:41.030
- Here's to you, boys!
- Time!

05:41.120 --> 05:43.190
- I'm away to my room.
- Thank you, Mr Bones.

05:43.280 --> 05:44.633
- Thank you, Bill.
- There you go!

05:44.720 --> 05:47.632
Don't forget to come back tomorrow
for our lunchtime special:

05:47.720 --> 05:49.597
- roast suckling--
- Huh?

05:49.680 --> 05:52.274
- Potatoes, sir. Potatoes.
- All right.

05:52.360 --> 05:55.193
No-- No offence, madam.
No offence.

05:57.520 --> 05:59.670
All right, boys.

05:59.760 --> 06:02.320
When you're finished here,
you can go and clean up in the kitchen.

06:02.400 --> 06:05.119
I left some table scraps
in there for your supper.

06:05.200 --> 06:07.760
Oh, yes, and, boys...

06:07.840 --> 06:10.400
last night you forgot
to put out the lantern!

06:10.480 --> 06:15.190
If you forget that again,
there'll be no table scraps for a week!

06:16.480 --> 06:18.869
You're standing on my ear.

06:18.960 --> 06:20.951
Easy. Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Easy, Rizzo!

06:21.040 --> 06:23.952
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
That's it. Steady.

06:24.040 --> 06:27.032
- I hate my life.
- I hate your life too.

06:27.120 --> 06:30.954
- If I had a life, I'd hate it.
- I should just run off to sea

06:31.040 --> 06:34.635
He was my age when he sailed
to China as a cabin boy

06:34.720 --> 06:36.631
Run off to sea
and just leave everybody?

06:36.720 --> 06:39.359
Who's everybody?
I'm an orphan. I've got no family.

06:39.440 --> 06:42.557
- Hey, you got us!
- Yeah, we're family. Got it.

06:47.520 --> 06:51.798
I mean, some family we are. Be serious,
Rizzo. We don't exactly look alike.

06:51.880 --> 06:56.954
Okay, all right. So I'm a rat and you're
a human being and Gonzo's a, uh--

06:57.040 --> 06:59.508
- Whatever.
- Yeah. We're still family.

06:59.600 --> 07:02.353
- Yeah.
- But I wish my life were more like...

07:02.440 --> 07:04.158
one of Captain Bones'
adventures...

07:04.240 --> 07:06.708
sailing the high seas and
searching for buried treasure.

07:06.800 --> 07:10.679
Yeah, discovering lost islands
and weird civilizations.

07:10.760 --> 07:13.911
Navigating with my father's old compass
to wherever the wind may take us.

07:14.000 --> 07:17.436
- Off to Zanzibar
to meet the Zanzibarbarians.

07:17.520 --> 07:19.590
To the southwest,
pirate galleons!

07:19.680 --> 07:22.877
To the southeast, multi-armed
Zanzibanian shark women...

07:22.960 --> 07:24.951
and their exploding wigs
of death!

07:25.040 --> 07:27.679
To the northwest,
dirty dishes!

07:27.760 --> 07:29.591
How does she do that?

07:29.680 --> 07:32.717
- Might as well start. I'll wash.
- Oh, yeah. I'll dry.

07:32.800 --> 07:34.597
I'll break.

07:38.520 --> 07:41.910
<i>I look around here</i>
<i>and I want to cry</i>

07:42.000 --> 07:43.831
Me too. Yeah.

07:43.920 --> 07:46.992
<i>I feel like the world</i>
<i>is passing me by</i>

07:47.080 --> 07:48.433
It is.

07:48.520 --> 07:50.954
<i>And I just can't</i>
<i>help but wonder</i>

07:51.040 --> 07:53.429
<i>Am I doomed to wash and dry</i>

07:53.520 --> 07:58.719
<i>And is it a curse I'm under</i>
<i>to do it till I die</i>

07:58.800 --> 08:01.268
- Oh, I hope not.
- Yeah.

08:01.360 --> 08:03.749
<i>- When I could be an explorer</i>
- Sure ya could.

08:03.840 --> 08:05.990
<i>- Sailing off to distant lands</i>
- Not so fast.

08:06.080 --> 08:07.911
<i>Instead of spending</i>
<i>every afternoon</i>

08:08.000 --> 08:10.070
<i>Just getting dishpan hands</i>

08:10.160 --> 08:14.392
<i>My future looks like nowhere</i>
<i>that I want to be</i>

08:14.480 --> 08:17.517
<i>There's gotta be</i>
<i>something better</i>

08:17.600 --> 08:19.033
<i>Something better</i>

08:19.120 --> 08:23.193
<i>There's gotta be something</i>
<i>better than this for me</i>

08:23.280 --> 08:24.918
Well, now you're talkin'.

08:25.000 --> 08:29.073
<i>If it's weird and wild</i>
<i>let's go and find it</i>

08:29.160 --> 08:31.913
<i>The crazier, the better</i>
<i>is what I say</i>

08:32.000 --> 08:33.399
Yeah, that's true.

08:33.480 --> 08:36.517
<i>To tell the truth</i>
<i>I really wouldn't mind it</i>

08:36.600 --> 08:37.510
Mind what?

08:37.600 --> 08:42.674
<i>If we found someplace</i>
<i>with ten square meals a day</i>

08:42.760 --> 08:44.591
<i>Let danger call my name</i>

08:44.680 --> 08:47.114
<i>If it does</i>
<i>I'm gonna hide</i>

08:47.200 --> 08:50.158
<i>I'll put my courage</i>
<i>to the test</i>

08:50.240 --> 08:52.310
<i>And I'll be</i>
<i>by your side</i>

08:52.400 --> 08:54.391
<i>He'll be by your side</i>

08:54.480 --> 08:59.554
<i>There's gotta be</i>
<i>something better than this</i>

08:59.640 --> 09:03.155
<i>- Something more than this</i>
<i>- I know that there's so much out there</i>

09:03.240 --> 09:06.073
<i>- To see</i>
<i>- To see</i>

09:06.160 --> 09:08.310
<i>And I know</i>
<i>this life I'm living</i>

09:08.400 --> 09:12.393
<i>Can't be my destiny</i>

09:12.480 --> 09:16.109
<i>There's gotta be</i>
<i>something better</i>

09:16.200 --> 09:17.918
<i>Something better</i>

09:18.000 --> 09:21.709
<i>There's gotta be something</i>
<i>better than this for me</i>

09:21.800 --> 09:25.190
- And me!
- Wait a minute. What about me?

09:25.280 --> 09:30.070
<i>There's something better</i>
<i>than this for you and</i>

09:30.160 --> 09:40.400
<i>Me</i>

09:40.480 --> 09:42.596
Enough of this singin'!

09:42.760 --> 09:45.433
Rum! I need rum, lads!

09:45.520 --> 09:48.830
I got the horrors!
Give me rum!

09:48.920 --> 09:50.558
Rum till I float!

09:50.640 --> 09:53.757
All right! All right!
Just one small one.

09:53.840 --> 09:56.479
Don't be giving him
any more rum!

09:56.560 --> 09:59.916
How does she blooming do that?

10:00.000 --> 10:01.274
Shh! Shh!

10:23.760 --> 10:29.118
Billy Bones!
It's me, Blind Pew.

10:29.200 --> 10:32.590
I know you're here, Billy.

10:32.680 --> 10:35.353
Ya snivelling coward!

10:35.440 --> 10:38.318
It's some kind
of a blind fiend.

10:38.400 --> 10:40.311
I believe they prefer
''visually challenged fiend.''

10:40.400 --> 10:45.190
Ah, I heard that!
There's someone here!

10:45.280 --> 10:47.510
Uh, no. Over here!

10:50.320 --> 10:52.231
Hmm, over here.

10:56.400 --> 11:00.075
Billy Bones! Ah,
I'd know that scurvy mug...

11:00.160 --> 11:03.197
of yours anywhere.

11:03.280 --> 11:05.191
Excuse me, sir,
but the bar is closed.

11:07.240 --> 11:11.199
Aha. A pretty
little girl, is it?

11:11.280 --> 11:15.193
Yes. Take me
to Billy Bones, my pet.

11:15.280 --> 11:16.952
Y-You've come
to the wrong place.

11:17.040 --> 11:19.918
Th-There's no Billy Bones here,
and I'm not a girl.

11:20.000 --> 11:25.120
Oh, I may be visually challenged,
but I can see you're lying.

11:25.200 --> 11:26.952
Huh?

11:28.880 --> 11:33.192
Good evening, Bill.
I know it's you.

11:33.280 --> 11:37.831
Yes. You thought you could
get away with it, didn't you?

11:37.920 --> 11:40.434
Just take it all
for yourself...

11:40.520 --> 11:44.718
and leave your shipmates
with nothing.

11:44.800 --> 11:48.429
We're not pleased with that,
Bill. Not at all.

11:48.520 --> 11:52.798
We want you to have this!

12:06.920 --> 12:09.150
Watch where you're going,
you stupid cat!

12:23.920 --> 12:26.309
The Black Spot!

12:34.960 --> 12:37.758
But I don't understand.
What is the Black Spot?

12:37.840 --> 12:40.400
The Black Spot's
a pirate's death sentence!

12:40.480 --> 12:44.473
- Fabulous.
- They'll be comin' to kill me tonight!

12:44.560 --> 12:46.391
- We'd better help.
- Yeah, yeah, let's get some stuff.

12:46.480 --> 12:49.916
- It's my sea chest them lubbers want.
- Underwear.

12:50.000 --> 12:53.913
But I'll trick them! I'll shake out
another reef and daddle 'em again!

12:54.000 --> 12:57.197
You wanna run that by us again
in English, Mr Bones?

12:57.280 --> 12:59.589
It's mine! I'm goin'
for that treasure myself!

12:59.680 --> 13:02.990
And no one-legged
son of a bilge rat will--

13:05.720 --> 13:06.869
Captain Bones!

13:08.360 --> 13:13.070
He died? And this is supposed
to be a kids' movie.

13:13.160 --> 13:16.232
Jimmy.Jim.
Jimmy,Jim,Jim,Jim,Jim.

13:16.320 --> 13:19.198
You always been a decent sort
to old Billy Bones.

13:19.280 --> 13:21.589
But I'm not Jimmy,Jim,Jimmy,
Jim,Jim,Jim,Jim.

13:21.680 --> 13:24.319
He's Jimmy,Jim,Jimmy,
Jim,Jim,Jim,Jim.

13:24.400 --> 13:25.833
-Jim!
- Yes, Captain.

13:25.920 --> 13:28.229
Jim,Jimmy,Jimmy,Jim,
Jim,Jim,Jim.

13:28.320 --> 13:30.550
- Yes, Captain. What is it?
- Take the map!

13:30.640 --> 13:32.949
- What map?
- The map to old Flint's treasure!

13:33.040 --> 13:34.871
Don't ya understand
what I been tellin' ya?

13:34.960 --> 13:38.236
I was Flinty's first mate!
We all were! Blind Pew and me!

13:38.320 --> 13:40.311
Me own shipmates,
they'll gully me for sure!

13:40.400 --> 13:42.356
And anybody else to get
their mitts on that map!

13:42.440 --> 13:44.476
A-And gullying hurts, right?

13:44.560 --> 13:46.516
Oh, aye! A lot!

13:46.600 --> 13:49.433
- So quick.
- Go to my sea chest! Get the map!

13:49.520 --> 13:51.397
Oh, yeah.

13:51.480 --> 13:55.439
- Oh, there. There.
- Oh, I think I've-- Oh, no.

13:55.520 --> 13:58.478
- Hey, guys, look!
- Rizzo!

13:58.560 --> 14:00.391
Oh, here!
How about this?

14:00.480 --> 14:02.391
Let's see.

14:04.520 --> 14:06.795
Hey, Rizzo, look.

14:13.600 --> 14:16.956
- It is a treasure map.
- We're gonna be rich.

14:17.040 --> 14:18.871
- We're gonna be dead.
- Beware, lads!

14:18.960 --> 14:20.951
Beware!

14:21.040 --> 14:23.508
- What? The one-legged man?
- Aye! But also...

14:23.600 --> 14:27.912
beware runnin' with scissors
or any other pointy objects.

14:28.000 --> 14:32.630
It's all good fun till
somebody loses an--

14:33.840 --> 14:35.671
Captain?

14:37.280 --> 14:40.317
We're standing in a room
with a dead guy!

14:45.720 --> 14:47.631
Jim!

14:56.880 --> 15:01.556
Oh, Billy Bones!
Trick or treat!

15:03.680 --> 15:05.989
Don't try to hide, Billy!
You know what we want!

15:13.160 --> 15:17.199
Where are ya, Billy Bones?
Where are ya, Billy?

15:18.880 --> 15:20.632
Mrs Bluveridge!

15:20.720 --> 15:24.554
There's no use in hiding!

15:24.640 --> 15:27.279
Can't a woman get her
beauty sleep any more?

15:28.400 --> 15:30.709
Jim, what you doing?

15:32.680 --> 15:34.875
Aha! Aha!

15:34.960 --> 15:37.793
Oh! Voila!

15:41.280 --> 15:43.510
- Okay, okay. I found the gun.
- Oh, now we gotta load it.

15:43.600 --> 15:46.068
- Okay.
- Oops.

15:47.920 --> 15:50.229
Okay, where does Mrs Bluveridge
keep the bullets?

15:50.320 --> 15:54.552
Billy's dead, and he hasn't
got the blooming map!

15:54.640 --> 15:57.108
- Those little girls must have it.
- Yeah!

15:57.200 --> 15:59.031
- Get them!
- Yeah!

15:59.120 --> 16:00.951
- Gonzo! Gonzo!
- What? What?

16:01.040 --> 16:03.918
I found the bullets. See?
Here they are. They--

16:04.000 --> 16:05.911
Oops.

16:06.000 --> 16:08.639
Open up in there!
We wants the map...

16:08.720 --> 16:11.598
and we'll skewer anybody
who gets in the way!

16:11.680 --> 16:14.353
Quick,Jim! The back stairs!

16:14.440 --> 16:16.271
Come on.

16:16.360 --> 16:17.918
Run! Run!

16:24.680 --> 16:27.592
Get out of my inn,
you tattooed miseries!

16:29.680 --> 16:31.989
Can't a woman
get a night's sleep alone?

16:32.080 --> 16:34.036
You come here, you!

16:36.280 --> 16:37.998
This gun is useless!

16:38.080 --> 16:42.198
- You lost all the bullets!
- Well, you're losin' the powder.

16:42.280 --> 16:44.794
The map!
Tell us where it is or die!

16:46.960 --> 16:48.791
- Get them!
- Run! Run, run, run!

16:53.280 --> 16:55.157
Hurry! Hurry!

16:55.240 --> 16:57.356
Hurry!

17:01.640 --> 17:03.756
Outta the way! Outta the way!
Get outta the way!

17:11.520 --> 17:12.999
Stop!

17:14.839 --> 17:17.637
Oh, Woof.

17:25.480 --> 17:27.948
Geronimo!

17:28.040 --> 17:29.109
Guys!

17:29.200 --> 17:30.838
Wow! What an exit!

17:30.920 --> 17:32.751
- Right through a brick wall!
- I am in such pain.

17:32.840 --> 17:34.876
Come on!

17:34.960 --> 17:39.829
I think I smell
something burning, no?

17:39.920 --> 17:42.036
What are we gonna do?
What are we gonna do?

17:43.240 --> 17:45.754
We can't go home, so--

17:47.160 --> 17:50.869
Oh, no. Uh-uh. No way. You're not
taking me on some crazy treasure hunt.

17:50.960 --> 17:53.679
- I am staying right here!
- Oh, good idea, Rizzo.

17:53.760 --> 17:56.638
Then you can see what half-burned,
vicious pirates look like.

17:56.720 --> 17:59.280
What are we waitin' for?
Gimme that map. Come on. Let's go.

17:59.360 --> 18:02.079
Wait a minute.
What about Mrs Bluveridge?

18:04.200 --> 18:06.555
I'll be fine, boys!
Run for it!

18:08.160 --> 18:10.549
How does she do that?

18:12.160 --> 18:14.071
Who's gonna clean
all this up?

18:16.640 --> 18:18.790
Two for a penny, sir?

18:18.880 --> 18:23.317
- I don't want a baked potato.
- Lovely hot baked potatoes.

18:25.360 --> 18:28.397
- Oh, let's see.
- What a night.

18:28.480 --> 18:30.550
- There it is!
- Huh? Oh.

18:32.920 --> 18:35.753
''Trelawny & Son
Master Ship Builders''

18:39.240 --> 18:41.595
Whoa, whoa!
Reality check here, guys!

18:41.680 --> 18:43.671
Do we actually believe some
bozo's gonna give us a ship...

18:43.760 --> 18:45.591
just because we show him
Captain Bones' map?

18:45.680 --> 18:50.834
- It's worth a try, Rizzo.
- I don't know.

18:50.920 --> 18:52.478
May I help you?

18:52.560 --> 18:56.997
Yes. Thank you. We wish to speak
with Squire Trelawney, the shipbuilder.

18:57.080 --> 18:59.036
- We need a ship.
- Ah, I'm sorry.

18:59.120 --> 19:02.317
The squire's in Long Neddry
for the grouse season.

19:02.400 --> 19:06.393
He will return
on the feast of St Lulu.

19:07.520 --> 19:09.431
- Thank you.
- That's that.

19:09.520 --> 19:11.431
Of course, his rich...

19:11.520 --> 19:16.230
half-wit son
young Squire Trelawney's here.

19:16.320 --> 19:18.788
We'll see him, then.

19:20.200 --> 19:21.872
Well, gentlemen...

19:21.960 --> 19:25.748
this is definitely a genuine,
bona fide treasure map.

19:27.080 --> 19:27.990
Really!

19:28.080 --> 19:29.752
Yes. Mr Bimbo told me so.

19:31.720 --> 19:36.396
Oh, Mr Bimbo lives in my finger.
He's very smart. He's been to the moon.

19:37.360 --> 19:38.873
Thank you. Twice.

19:40.280 --> 19:42.350
- I smell a bozo.
- Mm-hmm.

19:48.920 --> 19:51.275
Well done, Beakie.

19:51.360 --> 19:53.920
Now we know that is definitely
too much gunpowder.

19:55.400 --> 19:59.029
Beaker, stop fooling around.
We've got company.

20:01.760 --> 20:05.753
Oh, hello, chappies. Everyone, this is
Dr Livesey and his assistant, Beaker.

20:05.840 --> 20:08.149
They do research
and development for my papa.

20:08.240 --> 20:09.593
Hello.

20:09.680 --> 20:11.830
Actually, Squire, we were
hoping to meet your father.

20:11.920 --> 20:16.152
- We need a ship for an ocean voyage.
- Ocean? Ocean.

20:16.240 --> 20:21.189
- Ocean?
- You know, the ocean?

20:22.200 --> 20:25.795
Oh! Th-The big,
blue, wet thing! Yes!

20:26.800 --> 20:29.030
Say, I know
what's happening here.

20:29.120 --> 20:32.396
You chaps are planning
to sail to this island, aren't you?

20:32.480 --> 20:35.438
- To dig up this treasure.
- Yes, but we must be quiet about it.

20:35.520 --> 20:38.159
- There are pirates
looking for this map.

20:38.240 --> 20:40.470
Isn't that exciting?

20:40.560 --> 20:43.677
Pirates, eh?
Well, that settles it.

20:43.760 --> 20:45.591
We'll use one
of my daddy's boats...

20:45.680 --> 20:49.673
and I will personally finance
the voyage for the treasure myself.

20:49.760 --> 20:54.709
- You'll do that? Really?
- What are rich, half-wit sons for?

21:00.560 --> 21:02.869
Well, here's the dock.
Jim, where's our boat?

21:02.960 --> 21:04.951
We're on a dock?
No wonder I'm seasick.

21:05.040 --> 21:07.679
- Ahoy!
- Ah, morning, Squire.

21:07.760 --> 21:11.196
Welcome. Welcome.
Ah, there she is:

21:11.280 --> 21:13.236
the <i>Hispaniola</i>.

21:15.240 --> 21:17.151
Wow!

21:18.800 --> 21:22.076
- Come on. Let's go!
- Yeah, let's go.

21:29.680 --> 21:32.558
- ''Take a cruise,'' you said.
- Huh?

21:32.640 --> 21:35.108
- ''See the world,'' you said.
- Huh?

21:35.200 --> 21:39.034
Now here we are stuck
on the front of this stupid ship.

21:39.120 --> 21:42.908
Well, it could be worse.
We could be stuck in the audience.

21:44.480 --> 21:45.913
Well, Mr Bimbo...

21:46.000 --> 21:48.150
the ship is provisioned,
the crew is in place...

21:48.240 --> 21:50.879
and the captain should be
on board within the hour.

21:50.960 --> 21:52.871
You have been
a busy little man.

21:52.960 --> 21:56.953
- Oh, look, there goes Jim.
- Oh, yeah, yeah.

21:57.040 --> 21:59.508
Ooh! Ooh, look!

21:59.600 --> 22:01.511
It's the boat
steering thing.

22:01.600 --> 22:03.511
This is called the helm.

22:03.600 --> 22:07.513
Hey, how does it feel,
Captain Hawkins?

22:07.600 --> 22:09.909
Feels like
we're really doing it.

22:10.000 --> 22:12.958
It feels like we're finally
having an adventure!

22:13.040 --> 22:15.679
Yeah. I'm starvin'.
Where's the kitchen?

22:17.320 --> 22:19.038
<i>Heigh ho and up she rises</i>

22:19.120 --> 22:22.237
- Something smells good.
<i>- Heigh ho and up she rises</i>

22:22.320 --> 22:24.788
- Cool.
<i>- Heigh ho and up she rises</i>

