<i>till he's sober</i>

22:37.360 --> 22:39.191
<i>Early in the morning</i>

22:39.280 --> 22:42.397
What have we here?
Stowaways!

22:42.480 --> 22:46.712
I'm afraid we shish-kebab
and barbecue stowaways on this ship.

22:55.720 --> 22:57.995
Wait. I know.
You must be the cabin boys.

22:58.080 --> 23:01.117
- Yeah.
- Hungry, lads?

23:01.200 --> 23:04.317
Well, in my galley, you're always
welcome to help yourselves!

23:04.400 --> 23:06.709
Yes! Thank you!

23:09.000 --> 23:11.992
Oh, yes!

23:12.080 --> 23:15.152
Well, he's got a healthy appetite.
How about you, funny face?

23:15.240 --> 23:17.071
- Huh?
- Here.

23:17.160 --> 23:19.435
Hey. Thank you.

23:19.520 --> 23:21.909
My name is Gonzo,
and the guy in your chicken is Rizzo.

23:24.880 --> 23:29.112
- And you must be Master Hawkins.
- Yes, sir.

23:29.200 --> 23:32.636
Oh, you needn't be callin'
a lowly ship's cook ''sir.''

23:32.720 --> 23:36.679
Long John Silver,
at your humble service.

23:36.760 --> 23:39.354
We're just cabin boys,
Mr Silver.

23:39.440 --> 23:43.115
Long John to his friends.

23:43.200 --> 23:44.792
And believe me, lad...

23:44.880 --> 23:49.112
a friend you can trust
is worth his weight in gold.

23:49.200 --> 23:53.751
There's many a dark-hearted
scoundrel in these ports.

23:53.840 --> 23:55.831
Well, what do you mean?
Pirates?

23:55.920 --> 23:58.354
- Shh!
- Pirates! That's rich!

23:58.440 --> 24:01.273
Pirates? What an imagination.
Give me a cracker.

24:01.360 --> 24:04.477
Allow me to introduce
my pet lobster Polly.

24:04.560 --> 24:06.710
Pieces of eight!
Pieces of eight!

24:06.800 --> 24:08.631
Raised him
from a fingerling, I did.

24:08.720 --> 24:12.156
As fine a crustacean
as a man could ask for.

24:12.240 --> 24:15.198
B-But I thought sailors
had talking parrots as pets.

24:15.280 --> 24:17.430
Talking parrots?

24:17.520 --> 24:21.752
What an imagination.
First pirates, now talking parrots?

24:21.840 --> 24:25.753
What's next? A singing, dancing mouse
with his own amusement park?

24:25.840 --> 24:27.876
That's enough now, Polly.
Go on! Shoo!

24:30.960 --> 24:34.953
Right, me hearties. I'm gonna give you
a cook's tour of this fine ship.

24:35.040 --> 24:37.395
If you're gonna be the cook
on this ship, Mr Silver...

24:37.480 --> 24:39.835
I am definitely gonna need
bigger pants.

24:46.640 --> 24:48.471
What's the matter, lads?

24:51.600 --> 24:53.079
Oh, that?

24:53.160 --> 24:58.359
Lost that timber-fighting brigands
off Madagascar under Admiral Hawke.

24:58.440 --> 25:02.399
There's many a man lost a leg and worse
in the service of the king.

25:02.480 --> 25:07.031
Why, look what a cannibal
took off me...

25:07.120 --> 25:09.759
in exchange for me own life.

25:17.520 --> 25:19.715
Oh, you're a fine pair, lads.
That you are.

25:19.800 --> 25:22.917
Bright as buttons,
the lot of ye.

25:23.000 --> 25:25.798
- All hands on deck!
- Come on, then, lads.

25:27.120 --> 25:31.033
Chop-chop! Look lively now.
The captain will be here soon.

25:32.120 --> 25:33.792
Chop-chop.

25:36.320 --> 25:40.916
- Who's that?
- That is Mr Arrow, the first mate,

25:42.960 --> 25:45.793
The captain approaches.

25:50.000 --> 25:52.560
Move aside! Make way!
Make ready for the captain!

25:52.640 --> 25:54.676
Lollygaggers will suffer
his wrath!

25:54.760 --> 25:56.591
Wrath? I-Is this captain
bad-tempered?

25:56.680 --> 26:00.593
Is he bad-tempered?
The man is a raging volcano...

26:00.680 --> 26:04.434
tormented by inner demons the likes
of which mere mortals cannot fathom.

26:04.520 --> 26:06.556
He's got demons? Cool!

26:18.920 --> 26:20.831
Maniac!

26:43.720 --> 26:46.029
Heigh-ho, everyone.

26:46.120 --> 26:48.634
- What-- That--
- That's the raging volcano?

26:48.720 --> 26:52.474
- He's a frog.
- Maybe he gets hopping mad.

26:52.560 --> 26:54.471
Hopping mad.

27:01.800 --> 27:06.590
Piping aboard
Captain Abraham Smollett.

27:07.440 --> 27:09.351
Good day, Mr Arrow.

27:13.440 --> 27:16.557
I knew it.
He's furious.

27:16.640 --> 27:18.551
- Ah, you there!
- Me?

27:18.640 --> 27:21.916
You were in charge of railing dust.
Thirty lashes, and then

27:22.680 --> 27:27.879
- I didn't say that, Mr Arrow.
- I was anticipating your whim, sir.

27:29.200 --> 27:30.997
Oh. You must be
the cabin boys.

27:31.080 --> 27:33.230
- Yes, sir!
- Which one of you is Hawkins?

27:33.320 --> 27:35.151
I am, sir.

27:35.240 --> 27:37.390
I knew your father,Jim.
He was a good man.

27:37.480 --> 27:39.948
Thank you, sir.

27:40.040 --> 27:44.511
Well, this is shapin' up
to be a fine voyage, lads.

27:44.600 --> 27:47.068
Oh, yes, indeed.

27:49.920 --> 27:52.480
One leg,Jim.
Count 'em. One.

27:52.560 --> 27:56.348
- Remember what Billy Bones said.
- Oh, Gonzo, he seems all right.

27:56.440 --> 28:00.319
I mean, Long John's only a cook.
How dangerous could he be?

28:00.400 --> 28:03.198
Well, I don't know, but I--
Wait a minute. Where's Rizzo?

28:03.280 --> 28:06.238
Enjoy your cruise, sir.
Next!

28:06.320 --> 28:09.869
All right, folks, have your cheques
made out to ''Rat Tours Limited.''

28:09.960 --> 28:13.077
Remember, we put
the rat in ''pirate.''

28:14.520 --> 28:16.431
Why, thank you,
Mr Plagueman. Next!

28:16.520 --> 28:19.671
- Rizzo, what are you doing?
- What? Oh, this.

28:19.760 --> 28:21.591
Well, I figure
if the treasure map's a dud...

28:21.680 --> 28:25.639
the trip won't be a total loss,
financially speaking.

28:25.720 --> 28:29.110
Well, the wind seems to be freshening.
The tide is with us.

28:29.200 --> 28:32.033
Mr Arrow,
this voyage has begun.

28:32.120 --> 28:36.318
This voyage has begun!
Raise the gangplank!

28:36.400 --> 28:38.834
- Right, lads!
- Let go forward line!

28:38.920 --> 28:42.390
Let go aft line.
Hard to starboard.

28:42.480 --> 28:45.119
Any man caught dawdling
will be shot on sight.

28:45.200 --> 28:47.156
- I didn't say that.
- I was just paraphrasing.

28:47.240 --> 28:51.836
- Mr Arrow, just set the sails.
- Set the sails!

28:52.880 --> 28:54.791
Hey, where's my camera?

28:54.880 --> 28:58.395
- I'll miss you! I said I'll miss you!
- We'll send postcards!

