32:34.160 --> 32:36.628
Headless Bill.

32:41.200 --> 32:45.432
Big-Fat-Ugly-Bug-Face-
Baby-Eating O'Brien?

32:45.520 --> 32:46.873
Aye.

32:51.200 --> 32:53.873
- Angel Marie.
- Aye, aye.

32:58.480 --> 33:01.597
Gentlemen, may I see you
in my cabin?

33:01.680 --> 33:03.750
- Immediately?
- Mm-hmm.

33:03.840 --> 33:06.718
Who hired this crew? This is
undoubtedly the seediest bunch...

33:06.800 --> 33:08.870
of cutthroats, villains
and scoundrels I have ever seen!

33:08.960 --> 33:11.030
So who hired 'em?

33:17.040 --> 33:18.871
Your finger hired the crew?

33:18.960 --> 33:24.159
No, that's silly. The man who lives
in my finger hired the crew: Mr Bimbo.

33:24.240 --> 33:26.196
What? Ah!

33:26.280 --> 33:30.239
Yeah, he relied heavily on the advice
of our excellent cook, Long John Silver.

33:31.560 --> 33:35.030
A cook? And a guy who lives
in a bear's finger?

33:35.120 --> 33:36.997
Exactly!

33:38.960 --> 33:40.871
I'm starting to worry
about this voyage.

33:40.960 --> 33:43.713
Jim, I know Billy Bones
gave you the treasure map...

33:43.800 --> 33:46.633
but I hope you'll give it
to me for safekeeping.

33:46.720 --> 33:49.314
I'll be careful with it, sir.

33:56.480 --> 33:58.516
Beggin' your pardon,
gentlemen...

33:58.600 --> 34:00.955
but I've come with a bit
of a treat for you.

34:01.040 --> 34:04.077
'Tis my very own best brandy...

34:04.160 --> 34:07.311
laid down by the brothers
of Buckfast Abbey...

34:07.400 --> 34:10.233
vintage 1 737...

34:10.320 --> 34:13.232
to toast
to a prosperous voyage.

34:13.320 --> 34:16.312
- Oh, spiffy.
- I'm sorry, Mr Silver, but I'm not...

34:16.400 --> 34:19.039
going to allow drinking
on this voyage.

34:19.120 --> 34:22.078
- Oh, well, rules are rules.
- Oh, but, sir...

34:22.159 --> 34:25.436
'tis a tradition for the officers
to toast to the success of a voyage.

34:25.520 --> 34:26.998
Ah, very true.

34:27.080 --> 34:28.877
No, we must set an example
for this questionable crew.

34:28.960 --> 34:31.996
There will be no consumption
of alcohol of any kind.

34:32.080 --> 34:35.594
Oh, sir, but I can vouch
for this crew myself.

34:35.679 --> 34:38.478
You could sail to heaven
and back with these men.

34:38.560 --> 34:40.790
Well, I'm afraid
I must disagree with you.

34:40.880 --> 34:42.393
Oh.

34:42.480 --> 34:44.630
You wanna knock it off
with the booze?

34:44.719 --> 34:47.188
It's peeling the paint
off of the shuffleboard court.

34:47.280 --> 34:49.748
- Yeah.
- Sorry.

34:49.840 --> 34:51.831
And that's that.
This conversation is finished.

34:51.920 --> 34:53.956
I understand, sir.

34:54.040 --> 34:56.952
I shall tend to my duty
and see to it...

34:57.040 --> 35:01.113
that every drop of alcohol
is thrown overboard.

35:01.200 --> 35:04.636
Come on,Jim.
Don't bother, Captain.

35:04.720 --> 35:07.188
You can go
if you want to,Jim.

35:07.280 --> 35:09.111
- Come on.
- Yeah.

35:10.120 --> 35:13.271
Oh, well. I guess the human beings
wanna hang out together...

35:13.360 --> 35:15.271
don't wanna spend time
with a rat and a, uh--

35:15.360 --> 35:17.669
- Uh, uh, whatever.
- Yeah.

35:28.720 --> 35:30.870
- Say cheese!
- Cheese!

35:30.960 --> 35:33.110
Oh, that's great.

35:33.200 --> 35:35.111
Cute couple.

35:41.320 --> 35:44.232
Stop it!

35:44.320 --> 35:46.709
I never felt
like this before.

35:46.800 --> 35:48.631
- Denise, what I'm trying to say--
- Yes?

35:48.720 --> 35:50.551
- What I'm trying to say is--
- Yes?

35:50.640 --> 35:52.471
- What I mean to say is, I--
- Yes?

35:59.760 --> 36:02.228
I'm sorry your present
didn't work out.

36:02.320 --> 36:05.995
Oh,Jim, Smollett sails
by rules and laws.

36:06.080 --> 36:08.719
That's what bein' a captain's
all about.

36:08.800 --> 36:10.711
Me, I sails by the stars.

36:11.920 --> 36:14.593
Stars?

36:14.680 --> 36:18.355
North,Jim. Find me north out there
among them stars.

36:18.440 --> 36:20.396
Well, that's easy.

36:20.480 --> 36:22.391
Ah, yeah, but what
if you don't have a compass?

36:22.480 --> 36:24.789
Long John, please don't drop it.
It was my father's.

36:24.880 --> 36:26.711
It's all I have of his.
Please. Please.

36:28.360 --> 36:31.830
I'm sorry, lad.
I were only foolin'.

36:36.200 --> 36:38.714
- How old were you when he died, then?
- Seven.

36:42.880 --> 36:45.519
I were eight
when my father died at sea.

36:45.600 --> 36:50.071
- First mate, he was.
- My father was a first mate too.

36:50.160 --> 36:52.515
Was he, now?

36:52.600 --> 36:55.672
By the powers.
What a coincidence.

36:57.520 --> 37:02.799
Now,Jim, that be Polaris,
the North Star.

37:02.880 --> 37:06.395
Even in the China Sea,
that's north.

37:06.480 --> 37:08.948
- North. Polaris.
- Uh-huh.

37:09.040 --> 37:12.794
- So we must be heading southwest.
- Smart as paint you are, lad.

37:12.880 --> 37:15.599
Smart as paint.

37:15.680 --> 37:18.956
Now, that gets old Long John
to wonderin'.

37:22.760 --> 37:24.990
Why would we be
sailin' southwest?

37:26.560 --> 37:29.518
The scuttlebutt
among the crew is that, uh...

37:29.600 --> 37:31.670
we're sailin'
for buried treasure...

37:31.760 --> 37:34.877
and, uh, someone on board...

37:34.960 --> 37:36.871
has a map.

37:42.480 --> 37:45.278
'Course,
none of my concern,Jim.

37:45.360 --> 37:47.669
I'm just a ship's cook.

37:47.760 --> 37:51.673
Such matters are best suited
to Captain Smollett.

37:51.760 --> 37:54.877
Come on, Long John.
You could captain this ship.

37:54.960 --> 37:57.918
That I could, lad.

37:58.000 --> 38:00.150
Maybe someday I will.

38:11.120 --> 38:13.031
- Moonlight swim?
- Okay.

38:23.720 --> 38:25.995
Oh, Smolly, my love for you...

38:26.080 --> 38:28.640
is deeper than
the deep, blue sea.

39:08.880 --> 39:12.839
Get on with you! Go on!

39:12.920 --> 39:13.989
Hi,Jim!

39:14.080 --> 39:18.358
- Yo,Jimbo! Mornin', Long--
- Hi, Long John. Good morning.

39:18.440 --> 39:20.954
Well, at least one of us
is having a good time.

39:21.040 --> 39:24.396
Ah, Rizzo, it's not so bad.
Angel Marie said that later on...

39:24.480 --> 39:28.314
he'd throw a line out the back
and let me drag along the bottom.

39:28.400 --> 39:31.949
I don't know about this crew.
I feel like they're always

39:32.040 --> 39:34.235
That's just a figment
of your imagination.

39:38.400 --> 39:41.790
This is a figment
of my imagination?

39:41.880 --> 39:43.996
Now, tell us
where the map is...

39:44.080 --> 39:46.355
or we'll tear ya
limb from limb!

39:46.440 --> 39:48.715
Never. My friend
and I will never tell.

39:48.800 --> 39:51.360
Hey, hey, there could be
extenuatin' circumstances.

39:51.440 --> 39:53.715
I mean, you know--
Wh-- I b-- If--

39:53.800 --> 39:55.677
Maybe they'll ask
real nice.

39:55.760 --> 39:57.591
- In your dreams!
- Do it, Monty! Do it!

39:57.680 --> 39:59.989
Yeah, do it to me!

40:03.840 --> 40:05.751
Yes! More!

40:05.840 --> 40:08.798
- Oh, no, I can't look.
- Look at this!

40:08.880 --> 40:11.155
I'm taller!
This is so cool!

40:11.240 --> 40:14.357
I may even have a future
with the NBA.

40:14.440 --> 40:17.432
This won't work! He likes it!
Let's torture the rat!

40:17.520 --> 40:19.511
- Huh? No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no!
- Yeah!

40:19.600 --> 40:22.433
- Oh, no, no!
- Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah. Yes.

40:22.520 --> 40:25.557
- Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.
- Oh, please, no! I hate basketball!

40:25.640 --> 40:29.918
I got a lovely recipe
for blackened rat.

40:33.400 --> 40:35.834
I say!
This does not look safe!

40:39.600 --> 40:42.398
- What? What? What? What?
- I b-- I burned my hand.

40:42.480 --> 40:44.152
Kiss it or something!

40:48.720 --> 40:51.518
Poodly, poodly, poodly,
poodly, poodly.

40:51.600 --> 40:54.558
Mr Arrow, lock those three up
for the remainder of the voyage.

40:54.640 --> 40:56.471
- Yes, sir!
- You can't hold us!

40:56.560 --> 40:59.518
- To the brig! Move along!
- Will you stop crying!

40:59.600 --> 41:03.639
- Move along.
- Oh, good. That's good. Yeah.

41:03.720 --> 41:06.393
Master Hawkins, may I see you
in my cabin, please?

41:06.480 --> 41:09.278
Yes, sir.

41:09.360 --> 41:11.828
- Ready, Mr Gonzo?
- Ready!

41:11.920 --> 41:13.911
Tie off the rope, Beaker!

41:14.000 --> 41:18.516
We call this
the window shade cure.

41:18.600 --> 41:20.909
All right.
Snip, snip, snip.

41:23.680 --> 41:26.148
Oh, great! Wow!

41:30.720 --> 41:33.029
That was so cool!

41:33.120 --> 41:35.509
Hmm? Oh, sure.

41:39.360 --> 41:42.238
- Who's the lady pig, sir?
- Never mind that,Jim. Listen.

41:42.320 --> 41:45.756
I'm hoping you're willing
to give me the map now,

41:45.840 --> 41:47.751
I'd rather not, sir.

41:49.600 --> 41:51.511
I'd hoped it wouldn't
come to this,Jim, but...

41:51.600 --> 41:53.591
as captain, I order you
to give me the map.

42:01.040 --> 42:04.316
- Mr Arrow?
- Aye, aye, Captain.

42:04.400 --> 42:06.436
Lock up this treasure map.

42:08.240 --> 42:10.549
It will be safe
in here, sir.

42:45.880 --> 42:50.112
It's been six weeks
since we left England.

42:51.040 --> 42:53.474
Five days
since we had a breeze.

43:03.560 --> 43:05.471
No!

43:05.560 --> 43:07.073
I got the madness!

43:08.040 --> 43:09.632
I got cabin fever!

43:09.720 --> 43:12.439
I've got it too!

43:12.520 --> 43:15.318
Cabin fever!

43:15.400 --> 43:18.870
<i>I got cabin fever</i>
<i>It's burning in my brain</i>

43:18.960 --> 43:22.589
<i>I got cabin fever</i>
<i>It's driving me insane</i>

43:22.680 --> 43:26.355
<i>We got cabin fever</i>
<i>We're flipping our bandannas</i>

43:26.440 --> 43:29.750
<i>Been stuck at sea so long</i>
<i>that we have simply gone bananas</i>

43:36.280 --> 43:38.919
<i>We, we, we got cabin fever</i>

43:39.000 --> 43:40.956
<i>We lost what sense we had</i>

43:41.040 --> 43:44.350
<i>We got cabin fever</i>
<i>We're all going mad</i>

43:44.440 --> 43:48.035
<i>Grab your partner by the ears</i>
<i>Lash him to the wheel</i>

43:48.120 --> 43:51.351
<i>Do-si-do, step on his toe</i>
<i>Listen to him squeal</i>

43:51.440 --> 43:53.476
<i>Allemande left</i>
<i>Allemande right</i>

43:53.560 --> 43:55.630
<i>It's time to sail or sink</i>

43:55.720 --> 43:57.631
<i>Swing your partner</i>
<i>over the side</i>

43:57.720 --> 44:00.678
<i>- Drop him in the drink</i>
- We've got cabin fever.

44:00.760 --> 44:03.513
- No ifs, ands or buts.
- We're disoriented.

44:03.600 --> 44:05.955
- And demented.
- And a little nuts.

44:08.480 --> 44:09.993
<i>Volkswagen car</i>

44:13.040 --> 44:15.156
<i>We were sailing, sailing</i>

44:15.240 --> 44:17.151
<i>The wind was on our side</i>

44:19.000 --> 44:20.831
And then it died.

44:20.920 --> 44:24.037
<i>I got cabin fever</i>
<i>I think I lost my grip</i>

44:24.120 --> 44:28.159
<i>I'd like to get my hands</i>
<i>on whoever wrote this script</i>

44:28.240 --> 44:33.473
<i>I was floating</i>
<i>'neath the tropic moon</i>

44:33.560 --> 44:36.996
<i>And dreaming</i>
<i>of a blue lagoon</i>

44:37.080 --> 44:40.356
<i>Now I'm as crazy as a loon</i>

44:40.440 --> 44:44.115
<i>Cabin fever</i>
<i>has ravaged all aboard</i>

44:44.200 --> 44:47.397
<i>This one small vessel</i>
<i>has become a floating psycho ward</i>

44:47.480 --> 44:51.234
<i>We were sailing, sailing</i>
<i>heading who knows where</i>

44:51.320 --> 44:54.118
<i>And now though</i>
<i>we're all here</i>

44:54.200 --> 44:57.237
<i>We're not all there</i>

45:05.400 --> 45:07.755
Cabin fever!

45:08.760 --> 45:09.795
- The wind is back.
- What are we doing?

45:09.880 --> 45:12.189
What's goin' on here?

45:12.280 --> 45:14.589
- What was that?
- I feel like such a fool.

45:14.680 --> 45:18.116
- Yeah, me too.
- I hope nobody saw that. Embarrassing.

45:18.200 --> 45:20.111
- Get us outta here! Help!
- We didn't hit him!

45:20.200 --> 45:22.760
Come on. Let us out.
We was only joking.

45:24.440 --> 45:27.398
- Hey, Long John!
Hey, get us outta here!

45:27.480 --> 45:29.311
- Hey-ey-ey, Polly.
- What?

45:29.400 --> 45:32.676
- What was that song that just happened?
- What are you talkin' about?

45:32.760 --> 45:35.832
You know.
<i>Cabin Fever</i>

45:35.920 --> 45:38.912
- That.
- You see,John?

45:39.000 --> 45:42.117
You gotta get us outta here now!
Clueless is startin' to go crackers!

45:44.240 --> 45:46.071
Here you go.

45:46.160 --> 45:49.789
- Your bread and water for today.
- But I ordered shrimp scampi.

45:49.880 --> 45:53.668
It's more than you deserve,
ya villainous dogs!

45:53.760 --> 45:55.352
Oh,Jim.

45:55.440 --> 45:58.193
By rights,
I should be locked up too...

45:58.280 --> 46:00.999
for lettin' thieves like them
aboard this ship.

46:01.080 --> 46:03.230
Oh, it chills me...

46:03.320 --> 46:06.118
to think that they almost
killed your little friends...

46:06.200 --> 46:08.350
looking for some
daft treasure map.

46:08.440 --> 46:12.752
None of this would've happened if I'd
have given Captain Smollet the--

46:15.320 --> 46:17.390
What, lad?

46:17.480 --> 46:20.631
I'm not really sure I should be talking
about this with you or with anyone.

46:20.720 --> 46:25.396
You mean, you've really
got a treasure map?

46:25.480 --> 46:29.155
Not any more. Mr Arrow took it and
locked it up in the captain's cabin.

46:29.240 --> 46:31.071
You must promise
to keep it a secret.

46:31.160 --> 46:35.233
Don't bother your head about that.
You've only told old Long John.

46:35.320 --> 46:37.595
Now, you run along
and do your chores. Go on.

46:37.680 --> 46:39.557
Go on.

47:02.760 --> 47:04.716
Safely now. Safely.

47:08.360 --> 47:10.271
Steady as she goes.

47:13.200 --> 47:15.839
Oh. Mr Silver, good evening.

47:15.920 --> 47:18.195
Wicked fog tonight, sir.

47:18.280 --> 47:21.431
Reminds me of the night
we ran aground off the pampas.

47:21.520 --> 47:24.080
Half the crew drowned
in leaky lifeboats.

47:24.160 --> 47:25.991
Ah, it were
a terrible shame.

47:26.080 --> 47:29.231
- Leaky lifeboats?
- Oh, a common occurrence, sir.

47:29.320 --> 47:32.312
A little-used piece of equipment
falls into disrepair...

47:32.400 --> 47:36.359
- and becomes, shall we say--
- Unsafe?

47:36.440 --> 47:40.035
Oh, I'm not sayin'
our lifeboats are unsafe, sir.

47:40.120 --> 47:44.113
I'm not sayin'
we got problems--

47:44.200 --> 47:45.633
Still--

47:47.640 --> 47:48.709
Hmm. Hmm.

47:48.800 --> 47:52.998
The caulking appears tight.
No dampness under the gunwale.

47:53.080 --> 47:54.877
This one seems seaworthy.

47:54.960 --> 47:59.272
Well, sir, they do, of course, until
you get them out in the open ocean.

48:00.800 --> 48:03.189
- Cast me off, Mr Silver.
- Oh, yes, sir.

48:03.280 --> 48:08.513
Oh, sir, is there anything I can
hold for you for safekeeping?

48:08.600 --> 48:11.114
Your hat? Your coat?

48:11.200 --> 48:14.590
- Your keys?
- Hmm? My keys?

48:14.680 --> 48:19.674
Of course. If they were to fall
overboard, it would be disastrous.

48:19.760 --> 48:22.558
Oh, that it would, sir.

48:25.080 --> 48:26.638
Cast me off, Mr Silver!

48:26.720 --> 48:28.199
Aye, aye, sir!

48:29.360 --> 48:31.476
Thank you, Mr Silver.

48:31.560 --> 48:33.915
Just doin' my duty, sir.

48:38.320 --> 48:39.958
Oh, yes,John.

48:41.680 --> 48:44.638
Man overboard!

48:49.160 --> 48:50.070
Yes.

48:50.160 --> 48:51.991
- I'm sorry, sir.
- Wha--

48:52.080 --> 48:54.833
Mr Arrow's gone overboard,
and...

48:54.920 --> 48:57.388
all we found was his hat!

48:57.480 --> 48:59.198
Oh, no.

49:05.560 --> 49:10.395
And so, my friends, the sea has claimed
another loyal officer and friend.

49:10.480 --> 49:12.391
- This was a person who served--
- I got it! I got it!

49:12.480 --> 49:14.391
Okay, after you, Monty.

49:14.480 --> 49:17.119
- No, after you.
- Will you just come on.

49:17.200 --> 49:19.668
Mr Samuel Arrow,
a wonderful man who...

49:19.760 --> 49:22.718
used to get us up from our beds
before dawn for a good flossing.

49:24.840 --> 49:27.434
- Okay, okay. Now, spread out
and find the map.

49:27.520 --> 49:32.071
May the wind be ever at your back,
Samuel Arrow. Rest in peace, my friend.

49:32.160 --> 49:34.720
- Amen.
- Amen.

49:37.120 --> 49:39.236
Shh.

49:40.800 --> 49:43.189
- See? See?
- Wait. Open it. Open it.

49:43.280 --> 49:46.875
No, no, no, we gotta take it
to Long John. Come on.

49:54.320 --> 49:56.151
This apple has a worm in it.

49:56.240 --> 49:59.357
That's not a worm.
That's my tail.

49:59.440 --> 50:01.351
What's wrong?

50:02.440 --> 50:06.149
- It just feels so weird.
- You mean, that Mr Arrow's dead?

50:06.240 --> 50:10.916
Yeah, that, and my pants
are filled with starfish.

50:11.000 --> 50:13.070
You and your hobbies!

50:13.160 --> 50:15.355
Rizzo!

50:15.440 --> 50:18.716
-Jim, we've missed you! Climb in!
- Can't. I'm doing my chores.

50:18.800 --> 50:21.997
- Oh, come on. Share an apple.
- Yeah, come on!

50:25.440 --> 50:29.752
- Anyway, here's the plan.
- I say we should kill that captain now.

50:29.840 --> 50:33.389
- And then we'll get
that twit of a bear!

50:34.480 --> 50:36.391
Oh, hi, Long John.

50:38.480 --> 50:43.349
I'm an easy man.
A gentlemen of fortune, says most.

50:43.440 --> 50:46.637
But it makes me sick at heart
to sail with the likes of you.

50:47.920 --> 50:50.070
Now, get this straight.

50:50.160 --> 50:53.277
If anyone mutinies
before I says so...

50:53.360 --> 50:57.433
I'll throw you overboard
like I did that scurvy mate Mr Arrow!

50:57.520 --> 51:02.230
I says, let the captain
steer us closer to the island.

51:02.320 --> 51:04.231
I've got the lad's
treasure map now.

51:04.320 --> 51:06.550
When the time is ripe,
we'll kill 'em all!

51:06.640 --> 51:10.599
- That's what I said!
- That's what I said!

51:10.680 --> 51:14.070
- Land ho!
- Come on, lads! Let's go!

51:14.160 --> 51:16.071
Yea! Land ho!

51:19.680 --> 51:22.558
Oh, my goodness.

51:25.760 --> 51:27.318
Land ho!

51:28.720 --> 51:30.597
Beachfront property!

51:30.680 --> 51:32.511
Retirement estates!

51:32.600 --> 51:34.158
- Bikinis!
- Bikinis!

51:35.200 --> 51:37.839
Throw the mainsail!
Drop anchor!

51:37.920 --> 51:40.832
Bring her up
hard of starboard, helmsman.

51:48.440 --> 51:50.556
Bring those barrels
over here, lads!

51:51.800 --> 51:53.791
Helmsman, give a hand
with the longboats.

51:53.880 --> 51:56.189
- Captain, may I speak with you?
- I'm sort of busy right now,Jim.

51:56.280 --> 51:59.875
But, Captain, we just heard.
Long John is planning a mutiny,

51:59.960 --> 52:01.951
- Yeah.
- I see.

52:02.040 --> 52:04.634
- Mr Silver?
- Aye, aye, Cap'n!

52:04.720 --> 52:06.995
Mr Silver, I want you
to take the crew ashore at once.

52:07.080 --> 52:09.594
We need water and provisions.
Take as long as you want.

52:11.520 --> 52:14.637
Sir! 'Tis a task to my liking, sir.
That it is!

52:14.720 --> 52:18.110
- Quickly, boys. Gather the officers
and meet me in my quarters. Quickly.

52:19.400 --> 52:21.550
This is a lucky break.
Captain lettin' us go ashore.

52:21.640 --> 52:23.517
Us with the map and all.

52:23.600 --> 52:26.273
It's like giving the treasure to us
on a silver platter.

52:26.360 --> 52:31.036
Aye, that it is, Polly.
Never trust a silver platter.

52:35.560 --> 52:37.437
Follow me, Beakie. Come along.

52:39.160 --> 52:40.229
Jim, lad!

52:40.320 --> 52:44.154
There's room in the boat for one more.
Come along for an adventure.

52:44.240 --> 52:47.516
- I-I can't. The captain wants me.
- Oh, what a shame!

52:47.600 --> 52:49.955
I'll miss you, lad.
That I will.

52:50.040 --> 52:54.636
Um,Jim! I seem to have
left my crutch on board.

52:54.720 --> 52:56.790
Hand it to me like
a good lad, will ya?

52:59.920 --> 53:01.399
There's a good boy.

53:03.200 --> 53:05.998
Have to be a bit closer than that.
Can't reach it from there.

53:06.680 --> 53:08.830
- Oh!
- Oh! Ah!

53:08.920 --> 53:11.036
Cast away, men!
Be quick now!

53:11.120 --> 53:13.270
Go, go, go!
Don't splash!

53:16.080 --> 53:17.354
The plan is simple.

53:17.440 --> 53:20.512
Once the pirates are ashore,
we set sail and return in a year or so.

53:20.600 --> 53:23.672
- By then, all the fight
should be out of'em.

53:23.760 --> 53:24.988
That's a brilliant plan.

53:25.080 --> 53:27.036
- Except for one thing.
- What's that?

53:27.120 --> 53:29.680
The pirates have Jim!

53:45.400 --> 53:46.594
I'm tired!

53:46.680 --> 53:48.272
- You're what?
- I'm gettin' tired!

53:48.360 --> 53:51.830
- He says go faster.
- I'm gettin' tired!

54:05.600 --> 54:08.353
Hey, man! I can't figure out
what side we're on.

54:08.440 --> 54:11.079
Are we with the pirates
or the frog captain?

54:11.160 --> 54:13.151
Oh, hey, man,
just play the gig.

54:13.240 --> 54:15.356
Never get involved in politics.

54:15.440 --> 54:17.715
Politics!
Politics!

54:26.520 --> 54:28.033
Jim, lad!

54:35.520 --> 54:39.513
Easy,Jim.
'Tis all in good fun.

54:39.600 --> 54:44.230
Pleased I am to initiate you
into our enterprising, um, company.

54:46.480 --> 54:48.675
Which entitles you
to all the benefits thereof.

54:48.760 --> 54:54.232
- But I don't want any benefits.
- This is a one-time

54:54.320 --> 54:58.950
Say no, and I will be forced
to, um, terminate our relationship.

